<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 5:30PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Anson
and south central Richmond Counties through 630 PM EDT...
At 529 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Wadesboro, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Rockingham, Hamlet, Dobbins Heights, Lilesville, Morven, McFarlan,
Diggs, East Rockingham and Blewett Falls Lake.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
